.TH "get_ccwdev_by_busid" 9 "get_ccwdev_by_busid" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
get_ccwdev_by_busid \- obtain device from a bus id
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct ccw_device *" get_ccwdev_by_busid
.BI "(struct ccw_driver *cdrv "  ","
.BI "const char *bus_id "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "cdrv" 12
driver the device is owned by
.IP "bus_id" 12
bus id of the device to be searched
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function searches all devices owned by \fIcdrv\fP for a device with a bus
id matching \fIbus_id\fP.
.SH "RETURN"
If a match is found, its reference count of the found device is increased
and it is returned; else NULL is returned.
